> **Dissertation Research Project** — Hybrid Classical-Quantum Neural Network for binary classification of mammogram images (Benign vs Malignant), with noise robustness analysis across three quantum circuit architectures.

🔗 **Live Demo:** [explainable-noise-resilient-quantum.onrender.com](https://explainable-noise-resilient-quantum.onrender.com)

---

## 📌 Research Motivation

Standard CNNs classify breast cancer as a black box — they output a probability with no quantum interpretability. This project investigates whether **quantum circuits can extract meaningful diagnostic features** that classical neurons cannot, and whether **quantum expectation values ⟨Z⟩** carry physically interpretable information for medical imaging.

The CNN (DenseNet121) serves as a **classical baseline** to measure quantum advantage against — not as competition.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview

```
Mammogram Image (224×224)
        ↓
DenseNet121 Backbone (pretrained ImageNet)
        ↓
Classical Feature Vector (1024-dim)
        ↓
Pre-Quantum Compression Layer (Linear → BatchNorm → ReLU → Tanh)
        ↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         QUANTUM CIRCUIT LAYER            │
│  Config 1: Single Qubit (RX+RY+RZ)       │
│  Config 2: Entanglement Only (CNOT)      │
│  Config 3: Full Variational (R+CNOT)     │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
        ↓
Quantum Expectation Values ⟨Z⟩
        ↓
Post-Quantum Classifier + Bypass Connection
        ↓
Benign / Malignant
```

